# SDD Rules — {{ project_name }}

Always use Spec-Driven Development. Before any change, read:

1. `.specify/memory/constitution.md`
2. `.specify/specs/<active-spec>/spec.md`
3. `.specify/specs/<active-spec>/plan.md`
4. `.specify/specs/<active-spec>/tasks.md`

- `.specify/` is the source of truth.
- Only implement what is in `spec.md`.
- Work task by task from `tasks.md`.
- Only pending checks (`- [ ]`). Mark done only when truly complete.
- After each change: explain task completed + files modified.
- Conflict resolution: `constitution.md` > `spec.md` > `plan.md`.

